item.title: Predicting the 2020 Presidential Election using Support Vector Regression
item.description: Introduction I want to preface this by saying that this is a model that I created in college in one of my Machine Learning classes for a final project in 2016, but I figured it was cool enough to display publicly. Licenced by Tulane University Computer Science. Now it is 2021, and the 2020 Presidential Election has concluded. Let’s see how young Sam did on his ML model compared to what actually happened!
